defaultThe Commercial Broadcasters Association (COBA) is the industry body for multichannel broadcasters and their on-demand services in the UK. defaultQ1 defaultWhatdefault should the BBC be for and what should be the purpose of public service broadcasting?default1.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCommercial broadcasters in the multichannel sector are one of the fastest growing parts of the UK TV industry. The sector has doubled direct employment in the last decade, increased investment in UK content by 30% in the last three years, and increased commissioning from independent producers by 50% last year. The multichannel sector now accounts for 18% of all new UK TV production.
default 
default&#xa0;default1.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThis growth 
defaultfuels 
defaultthe UK’s 
defaultstatus 
defaultas 
defaulta 
defaultglobal TV hub. The multichannel sector now has a turnover of £5 billion a year, helping provide the UK with the critical mass it needs to compete with 
defaultother 
defaultmajor media 
defaultcentres
default around the world. And, with 
defaultmany having
default 
defaultstrong 
defaultinternational networks, multichannel broadcasters 
defaulthelp drive exports of UK content, 
defaultreinvesting that income into UK production. Last year, 
default35% 
defaultof multichannel commissions in the UK were part funded through their international divisions.
default 
default&#xa0;default1.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn many areas, this commercially-funded content 
defaultis comparable to 
defaultPSB content. Sky’s commitment 
defaultto the arts includes 
defaultcommission
defaulting
default The South Bank Show, while Disney funds the production of Art Attack, historically commissioned by PSBs. But just as importantly, non PSB broadcasters add diversity. For example, according to producers body Pact, the multichannel sector commissions a substantially higher proportion of UK content from smaller producers than PSBs. 
defaultThis creates more opportunities for SMEs in the supply base. 
defaultPact’s census states that 34% of 
defaultmultichannel spend
default went on producers with a turnover of less than £25m per annum. This compares to 16% at the BBC, 8% at Channel 4, 19% at 
defaultFive
default and 11% at ITV.
default 
default&#xa0;default1.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe therefore believe that the future of the BBC needs to be seen within the changing landscape of the UK
default’s
default TV sector. The UK is 
defaulta more
default mixed, more global ec
defaultology than ever before. The 
defaultBBC ha
defaults a key role to play, as do 
defaultcommercial broadcasters
default and others
default. Maintaining a healthy, competitive market that enables a range of players to develop is 
defaultkey
default to fut
defaulture growth, and robust governance of the BBC is key to this.
default&#xa0;default1.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe comment on the nature of the BBC’s public purposes below.
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;defaultQ2 defaultHowdefault well has the BBC performed in the current Charter period in achieving its mission and public purposes? Are the public purposes in the current Charter the right ones? How might they change?default&#xa0;default2.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe number of the BBC’s public purposes –
default 
defaultin addition to other goals set by the Trust – can dilute the BBC’s impact 
defaultand 
defaultis at times conflicting. For example, BBC Worldwide 
defaulthas a public purpose to 
defaultpromote the BBC brand through its overseas channels. However, broadcasting BBC programmes on those channels, rather than selling them to third-party channels
default on a commercial basis
default, 
defaultrisks 
defaultr
defaultestricting
default the amount of revenues 
defaultWorldwide
default is able to return to the BBC from exploiting its IP.
default&#xa0;default2.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe believe that it is worth considering whether the number of overall purposes should be limited, or the priority of relevant purposes should be made clearer for each service.
default&#xa0;defaultQ3 What scope, scale and remit should the BBC have?default&#xa0;defaultShould the BBC’s output and services be provided to any greater or lesser degree for particular audiences?default&#xa0;defaultWhat balance should be struck in what the BBC produces in-house, commissions externally and leaves entirely to others to create?default&#xa0;defaultScope, scale and remit
default&#xa0;
default3.1
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe are concerned about proposals to augment certain BBC services
default. Firstly, the Government has put forward proposals to enhance PSB prominence requirements. Currently, 
defaultPSB services 
defaultare entitled to privileged positions 
defaulto
defaultn the Electronic Programme Guide 
default(EPG) 
defaultfor TV channels. The new proposals are focused on extending the prominence of PSBs onto on-demand platforms. While we appreciate the 
defaultimportance of 
defaultsuch services be
defaulting
default 
defaultreadily 
defaultavailable, we are not convinced that 
defaultthere is a need for 
defaultlegislation
default, as PSB on-demand services are widely used already.
default&#xa0;default3.2
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultW
defaulte therefore ask the Committee to call on 
defaultthe Government, a
defaults part of the DCMS’s forthcoming 
defaultconsultation on these proposals, 
defaultto consider a) whether PSB services are already 
defaultreadily 
defaultavailable on on-demand platforms and b) whether extending prominence in this way would have a negative impact on innovati
defaulton
default 
defaultby crowding out 
defaultnew services. 
default&#xa0;default3.3
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIn addition, as part of these proposals, the Government is also considering enhancing PSB pr
defaultominence 
defaulton well-established linear TV platforms. Proposals to take a more prescriptive definition of ‘appropriate prominence’ under the 2003 Communications Act would move the BBC children’s channels to the top of the Sky children’s section. This would have a negative impact on investment in UK children’s 
defaultcontent,
default as such a move would inevitably 
defaultmean moving
default other channels down, reducing their audience share and impacting on their content budgets. 
default&#xa0;default3.4
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOver the last three years, COBA children’s channels have increased their investment in UK children’s content by 60%, to 
defaultnearly 
default£30m.
default This has gone a long way to replace declines in children’s investment 
defaultat commercial PSBs
default, but this commissioning would be likely to be damaged by forcing those channels to move down the EPG. In contrast, the BBC does not depend on its EPG position to determine its income, which of course comes from the licence fee. 
default&#xa0;default3.5
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthe BBC children’s channels already have privileged prominence, being entitled to the best available slots (non PSB channels go automatically to the bottom of the EPG section when launching). 
default&#xa0;default3.6
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultP
defaulterhaps most importantly, 
defaulthowever, 
defaultthe BBC children’s channel
defaults
default are already highly successful, being the most watched channels in their demographics. The Director General 
defaultoutlined their success 
defaultto the Committee in October, saying:
default&#xa0;
default“So 
defaultNewsround
default now is not on BBC One but the figures for 
defaultNewsround
default are growing. Likewise with Blue Peter the figures are growing, so these two channels are working and they’re finding their audience.”
default&#xa0;default3.7
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAnne 
defaultBulford
default, the BBC’s 
defaultManaging Director, Operations and Finance, 
defaultexpanded on this
default in her evidence
default, saying: 
default&#xa0;
default“[C]
defaulthildren’s
default awareness of children’s channels and digital channels is very high and 
defaultCbeebies
default and CBBC are the first place they go, so nought to six 95% of them are aware of it and six to 12s 89% are aware of CBBC, so I think that’s very encouraging. Where the channels are, how we cross-promote them, how we take people to those channels is what’s important and everything Tony said about the app and how its broken up I think shows that content is very key and children love it and they find it and they come to it.”
default&#xa0;default3.8
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe therefore ask the Committee to call on the Government, as part of any consultation on these proposals, to consider 
defaultfully the impact of investment i
defaultn UK’s children’s content.
default&#xa0;default3.9
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSeparately, the BBC recently announced a raft of changes to 
defaulton-demand services
default, including extending the 
defaultiPlayer
default 
defaultcatch-up window from seven to 30 days, premiering content on the 
defaulti
defaultP
defaultlayer
default before it has been broadcast on linear channels, and a download
default-
defaultto
default-
defaultown service, BBC Store. Taken together, these are potentially significant moves in the market and could have a negative impact on commercial services. 
defaultThey also entail, in our view, substantial changes to the current service. 
defaultWe will be asking the Trust to investigate the market impact of these proposals fully, and ask the Committee to support our request for a full Public Value Test.
default&#xa0;default3.10
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultHowever, the manner in which these services were announced, without full scrutiny by the Trust, does also in our view raise questions over the oversight of the BBC, as we outline in response to Question 7.
default 
